text: Grain-based diets are often used in preclinical research, but vary from batch-to-batch. Identifying a purified diet with optimal fiber composition would aid in standardization & reproducibility of studies on gut physiology/microbiota. @AppEnvMicro: https://t.co/UTft3nPSur https://t.co/qrrI8MT0cX

Statistical differences were determined using a one-way analysis of variance (ANOVA) with Tukey's post-hoc test. text: Research in @JournalSpectrum provides compelling evidence on the efficacy of Far-UVC light (222 nm) for killing clinically significant antibiotic-resistant bacteria on diverse material surfaces. Read the article: https://t.co/DcZQ2MudGo https://t.co/ayVpPn6ENd
media: [{'display_url': 'pic.x.com/ayVpPn6ENd', 'expanded_url': 'https://x.com/ASMicrobiology/status/1853831130664837460/photo/1', 'ext_alt_text': ' Disinfection by UVC light on melamine board. (A) MRSA. (B) VRE species. (C) CREC. (D) CRKP. (E) CRPA. (F) CRAB. The effectiveness of Delta U+ Disinfection Device Care 222 in reducing various strains of bacteria was expressed in log10 of colony count. The colony count of alcohol-treatment groups was converted into log10 value and illustrated by green bars. text:
On this #VeteransDay, learn how HHMI astrophysicist Marla Geha at @Yale is working to empower veterans to channel their skills & experience into impactful careers in STEM.

She launched a first-of-its-kind program for veterans in their undergraduate years: https://t.co/hGJqhHKG6I https://t.co/KQx7fyBJus

‚ÄòI'm always thankful for science and parenting because the two really helped each other in my career. Raising children & mentoring them to grow into young adults ‚Äì or mentoring graduate students ‚Äì requires one particular moment in time that you let go a little bit.‚Äô ‚Äì Huda Zoghbi https://t.co/pCoQdaRsR6

Happy #STEMDay!üåü  Our investigators and their labs are exploring the wonders of basic science, from immune systems to ancient organisms. It‚Äôs all about curiosity, discovery, and having fun! üåçüî¨ https://t.co/PxCD5QOU8H
‚ÄúReally, my definition of basic science is: decoding the language of life‚Äù ‚Äì Huda Zoghbi, HHMI Investigator, on why basic science touches everyone. https://t.co/5MFOchTPX9

‚ÄúI am very privileged to have a chance to take care of patients and also run a research laboratory. It's fascinating to probe into nature, but also have a direct patient impact.‚Äù ‚ÄìHoward Chang, HHMI Investigator at Stanford University School of Medicine. https://t.co/CKsUaTtIq0 https://t.co/VyOpEHw3T8

üî¨ Microscope or telescope? üî≠ 

Stars above, stars below! Here we‚Äôre looking down‚Äîinto the hidden universe on a leaf! This microscopic view reveals star-shaped trichomes, ‚Äúbreathing‚Äù pores, and a branching vein on a showy deutzia leaf. üçÉ

text:
Cancer breaks all kinds of rules. New studies explore one of its cheats: ecDNA, stashed outside chromosomes, helps a tumor evolve to overcome threats from the immune system and from treatment. 

Read more: https://t.co/imlPwxArOc https://t.co/FHtrAXlWuQ
